
[1]bastile

   BAS'TILE, n. An old castle in Paris, built between 1369 and 1383, used
   as a state prison, and converted to the purpose of confining men for
   life, who happened to incur the resentment or jealousy of the French
   monarchs. It was demolished by the enraged populace in 1789.
